Reasoning: The paper deals with wireless communication systems and signal processing techniques, which are typically covered under the Information Theory (cs.IT), Communications (cs.COMM), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of large-scale MIMO and multi-carrier waveforms also suggests that the paper may fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the development of low-complexity data detection algorithms for these waveforms may also make the paper relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
